code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const single = ref('overview')
  const multiple = ref(['email'])
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxFlatRadio v-model="single">
      <TxFlatRadioItem value="overview" label="Overview" />
      <TxFlatRadioItem value="activity" label="Activity" />
      <TxFlatRadioItem value="settings" label="Settings" />
    </TxFlatRadio>

    <TxFlatRadio v-model="multiple" multiple>
      <TxFlatRadioItem value="email" label="Email" />
      <TxFlatRadioItem value="push" label="Push" />
      <TxFlatRadioItem value="sms" label="SMS" />
    </TxFlatRadio>
  </template>
---
:::

When the container is focused:

| Key | Behavior |
|-----|----------|
| `→` / `↓` | Select next non-disabled item (wraps) |
| `←` / `↑` | Select previous non-disabled item (wraps) |
| `Home` | Select first non-disabled item |
| `End` | Select last non-disabled item |
| `Enter` / `Space` | In `multiple` mode, toggle the currently focused item |

## API

### TxFlatRadio

#### Props

| Prop | Description | Type | Default |
|------|-------------|------|---------|
| `modelValue` / `v-model` | Selected value in single mode, or selected value array in `multiple` mode. | `string \| number \| (string \| number)[]` | - |
| `multiple` | Enables checkbox-like multi-select behavior. The sliding single-select indicator is hidden in this mode. | `boolean` | `false` |
| `disabled` | Disables the entire group, removes focusability, and blocks click / keyboard changes. | `boolean` | `false` |
| `size` | Size variant. | `'sm' \| 'md' \| 'lg'` | `'md'` |
| `bordered` | Adds an outer border around the selector. | `boolean` | `false` |

#### Events

| Event | Description | Params |
|-------|-------------|--------|
| `update:modelValue` | Emitted with the next selected value or selected value array. | `(value: string \| number \| (string \| number)[]) => void` |
| `change` | Emitted with the same payload after a selection change. | `(value: string \| number \| (string \| number)[]) => void` |

#### Slots

| Slot | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `default` | `TxFlatRadioItem` children. |

### TxFlatRadioItem

#### Props

| Prop | Description | Type | Default |
|------|-------------|------|---------|
| `value` | Item value registered with the parent selector. | `string \| number` | *required* |
| `label` | Fallback visible text when no default slot is provided. | `string` | - |
| `icon` | Fallback icon CSS class when no `icon` slot is provided. | `string` | - |
| `disabled` | Disables this item and skips it during keyboard navigation. | `boolean` | `false` |

#### Slots

| Slot | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `default` | Custom visible item content, replacing `label`. |
| `icon` | Custom icon content, replacing the `icon` class. |

## Interaction Contract

- Single-select mode uses `role="radiogroup"` on `TxFlatRadio` and `role="radio"` on each item.
- Multiple mode uses `role="group"` on the container and `role="checkbox"` on each item; the sliding indicator is hidden.
- Item buttons keep `tabindex="-1"`; focus stays on the container so arrow keys can drive the whole group.
- Arrow keys, Home, and End skip disabled items and wrap across enabled items.
- In multiple mode, arrow keys move the focused value and Enter / Space toggles it. In single mode, arrow keys immediately select the next value.
- Group-level `disabled` sets container `tabindex="-1"`, marks all items disabled, and blocks click / keyboard changes.

## Best Practices

- Use FlatRadio for two to five short options where immediate comparison matters. Prefer `TxSelect` for longer option lists.
- Keep labels short enough to stay on one line; the item layout intentionally uses `white-space: nowrap`.
- Avoid mixing long custom slot content with icons in compact `sm` size.
- Use `multiple` only when the selected values are independent toggles; otherwise use separate switches or checkboxes with clearer labels.
- Keep `value` stable across renders because the parent registers item DOM by value for indicator and keyboard ordering.

## Review Notes

- **Accessibility note:** The group is the only tabbable element; item buttons are kept at `tabindex="-1"` so arrow-key handling stays centralized. Use nearby field text or an external label to name the group.
- **Verified coverage:** `flat-radio.test.ts` covers single-select `radiogroup`/`radio` semantics, item disabled state, disabled group focus removal, arrow-key wrapping while skipping disabled items, Home/End selection, and Enter/Space toggling in `multiple` mode.

